SUMMARY:We Read Wednesdays with Empowering Readers OC
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T120000
DTSTAMP:20260327T190003Z
UID:1ef55b80c01657b5b787673aabf4e099@family-events-agent
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:children,play,toddler,museum,family
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nAges: 0-6
 0 months\\nCategory: Play\\n\\nPretend City Children’s Museum and Parent
 is Foundation are partnering for something truly magical at We Read Wedne
 sdays\, where Littles and Grans read together! Our wonderful Empowering 
 Readers OC reading mentors are bringing the joy of storytelling into the p
 layful world of Pretend City\, where imagination comes alive and every cor
 ner invites discovery.\nThis partnership is so important because it introd
 uces children to the love of books in a way that feels fun\, welcoming\, a
 nd shared. When young learners and older adult mentors gather in a place b
 uilt for wonder\, stories become more than words on a page. They become mo
 ments of connection\, confidence\, and inspiration across generations.\nTo
 gether\, Pretend City and Empowering Readers OC are creating a community w
 here reading is joyful and every story sparks a love of reading.\n\nTIME:
  11am &#8211\; 12pm\nAbout the Play Partner:\nEmpowering Readers OC\, a pr
 ogram of Parentis Foundation\, provides evidence-based literacy interventi
 on and intergenerational mentoring to students in grades 1–5 who are rea
 ding below grade level. By pairing trained older adult volunteers with stu
 dents\, the program builds strong reading skills\, confidence\, and a foun
 dation for lifelong learning.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.pretendcity.org/
 events/we-read-wednesdays-with-empowering-readers-oc/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/we-read-wednesdays-with-empowering-
 readers-oc/
